  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "OPERATION EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>· <strong>Operations & Logistics Management:</strong> Oversee daily receiving, warehousing, and distribution, including managing shipping documentation and coordinating with couriers/suppliers.</p><p>· <strong>Inventory Control:</strong> Perform cycle counts, reconcile stock, manage inventory data, and maintain 100% accuracy in stock records, including handling damages and returns.</p><p>· <strong>Process Optimization:</strong> Implement, improve, and document warehouse procedures, layout, and storage techniques to maximize space utilization.</p><p>· <strong>Safety & Security Compliance:</strong> Enforce Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) regulations, conduct risk assessments, and maintain a safe, clean working environment.</p><p>· <strong>Team Leadership:</strong> Supervise, train, and schedule warehouse personnel, including handlers and forklift drivers.</p><p>· <strong>Reporting:</strong> Prepare reports on KPIs, warehouse performance, and inventory levels. </p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>· <strong>Experience:</strong> Previous experience in warehousing, logistics, or supply chain management.</p><p>· <strong>Skills:</strong> Proficient in inventory software/WMS, strong organizational skills, and technical knowledge of material handling equipment (MHE).</p><p>· <strong>Physical Ability:</strong> Ability to handle, lift, and move goods (often up to 30kg) and work in specific environments like cold rooms.</p><p>· <strong>Qualifications:</strong> Typically requires a Diploma in Logistics, Supply Chain, or equivalent, or relevant experience. </p><p><strong>Common Tasks</strong></p><p>· Monitoring inventory levels and stock movement.</p><p>· Arranging cargo for local and international delivery.</p><p>· Handling documentation for incoming and outgoing goods.</p><p>Operating warehouse machinery (e.g., forklift, reach truck). </p>",
